abstract: A survey, part of a new monthly series of surveys, found that respondents overwhelmingly selected Wal-Mart as the best corporate symbol of America today.
snippet: A survey, part of a new monthly series of surveys, found that respondents overwhelmingly selected Wal-Mart as the best corporate symbol of America today.
lead_paragraph: Coming together to poll average Americans, Vanity Fair and “60 Minutes” have concluded it’s a Wal-Mart Nation.

headline.main: Vanity Fair and ‘60 Minutes’ Are Polling the People
headline.print_headline: Vanity Fair and ‘60 Minutes’ Are Polling the People
